Midnight Oasis - Advanced
items.long_description_html:
Lachlan, the author, explains this script better than I can:

"The Midnight Oasis is a script about doing. While there are some information roles, the script is defined by power characters that have significant, exciting effects on the game - Farmer, Golem, Engineer, Professor, Poppy Grower, Pit-Hag & Psychopath among them. The first day of Midnight Oasis will (usually, hopefully) be a relaxing one for the evil team. There will be few, if any, information leads pointing in their direction. From there, it typically becomes a race. Powerful abilities will start to come online, good characters will start proving themselves. Power clashes with power. A careless evil team may find their Demon cornered, with nowhere to hide. A careless good team may find themselves decimated in the blink of an eye."

Also, if you claim King in this game, you have the option of wearing a Burger King or Medieval Times crown.  And if a Vizier is in the game, they can wear an upside-down crown. Together we will bring Arthurian legend to life!

items.name: Archiving Blood on the Clocktower and the Player Experience
items.description: A panel to discuss the importance of capturing player experiences and how archivists like myself preserve not just analog materials (such as video games, board games, etc) but how supplemental materials like oral histories help support the future memory of said game. An open dialogue focusing on how we can best ensure the game we love exists in a form we know it, in perpetuity.
